{"title_page": "Dryobalanops beccarii", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n|image =\n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref =\n|genus = Dryobalanops\n|species = beccarii\n|authority = [[William Turner Thiselton (Thistleton) Dyer|Dyer]]<ref name = Ashton/>\n|synonyms = *''Dryobalanops beccariana'' {{Au|[[Henry Nicholas Ridley|Ridl.]]}}, \n*''Dryobalanops oiocarpa'' {{Au|[[Dirk Fok van Slooten|Slooten]] ex [[Karel Heyne|K.Heyne]]}}, \n*''Dryobalanops oocarpa'' {{Au|Slooten}}.\n}}\n\n'''''Dryobalanops beccarii''''', or '''Kapur Keladan''', is a species of plant in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. The species is named after [[Odoardo Beccari]], 1843\u20131920, an Italian explorer and botanist. It is found in [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Borneo]]. It is a large [[Rainforest#Emergent layer|emergent]] tree, up to 65 m tall, found in mixed dipterocarp forests on shallow leached soils over both sandstone and shale.<ref name = Ashton/> It is a heavy hardwood sold under the trade names of  '''Kapur'''. It is recorded from at least four protected areas ([[Bako National Park|Bako]], [[Gunung Mulu National Park|Gunung Mulu]], [[Crocker Range National Park|Crocker Range]] and [[Temburong|Ulu Temburong]] National Parks).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | refs =\n<ref name=Ashton>{{Cite book | last1 = Ashton | first1 = P. S. | date = September 2004 | contribution = ''Dryobalanops beccarii'' Dyer | contribution-url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/backup/TFSS.vol4_5_6.pdf | editor1-last = Soepadmo | editor1-first = E. | editor2-last = Saw | editor2-first = L. G. | editor3-last = Chung | editor3-first = R. C. K. | title = Tree Flora of Sabah and Sarawak | volume = 5 | pages = 131\u2013132 | publisher = [[Forest Research Institute Malaysia]] | isbn = 983-2181-59-3 | url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | version = (free online from the publisher, lesser resolution scan PDF versions) | accessdate = 11 November 2007 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130927074942/http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | archive-date = 27 September 2013 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n}}\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Dryobalanops beccarii'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T33163A9763363 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/33163/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33163A9763363.en | access-date = 23 December 2017}} Listed as Endangered (CR A1cd+2&nbsp;cd D v2.3)\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5309748}}\n\n[[Category:Dryobalanops|beccarii]]\n[[Category:Trees of Peninsular Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Flora of Sabah]]\n[[Category:Endangered flora of Asia]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n|image =\n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref =\n|genus = Dryobalanops\n|species = beccarii\n|authority = [[William Turner Thiselton (Thistleton) Dyer|Dyer]]<ref name = Ashton/>\n|synonyms = *''Dryobalanops beccariana'' {{Au|[[Henry Nicholas Ridley|Ridl.]]}}, \n*''Dryobalanops oiocarpa'' {{Au|[[Dirk Fok van Slooten|Slooten]] ex [[Karel Heyne|K.Heyne]]}}, \n*''Dryobalanops oocarpa'' {{Au|Slooten}}.\n}}\n\n'''''Dryobalanops beccarii''''', or '''Kapur Keladan''', is a species of plant in the [[Dipterocarpaceae]] family. The species is named after [[Odoardo Beccari]], 1843\u20131920, an Italian explorer and botanist. It is found in [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Borneo]]. It is a large [[Rainforest#Emergent layer|emergent]] tree, up to 65 m tall, found in mixed dipterocarp forests on shallow leached soils over both sandstone and shale.<ref name = Ashton/> It is a heavy hardwood sold under the trade names of  '''Kapur'''. It is recorded from at least four protected areas ([[Bako National Park|Bako]], [[Gunung Mulu National Park|Gunung Mulu]], [[Crocker Range National Park|Crocker Range]] and [[Temburong|Ulu Temburong]] National Parks).\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | refs =\n<ref name=Ashton>{{Cite book | last1 = Ashton | first1 = P. S. | date = September 2004 | contribution = ''Dryobalanops beccarii'' Dyer | contribution-url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/backup/TFSS.vol4_5_6.pdf | editor1-last = Soepadmo | editor1-first = E. | editor2-last = Saw | editor2-first = L. G. | editor3-last = Chung | editor3-first = R. C. K. | title = Tree Flora of Sabah and Sarawak | volume = 5 | pages = 131\u2013132 | publisher = [[Forest Research Institute Malaysia]] | isbn = 983-2181-59-3 | url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | version = (free online from the publisher, lesser resolution scan PDF versions) | accessdate = 11 November 2007 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130927074942/http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | archive-date = 27 September 2013 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n}}\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Dryobalanops beccarii'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T33163A9763363 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/33163/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33163A9763363.en | access-date = 23 December 2017}} Listed as Endangered (CR A1cd+2&nbsp;cd D v2.3)\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5309748}}\n\n[[Category:Dryobalanops|beccarii]]\n[[Category:Trees of Peninsular Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Flora of Sabah]]\n[[Category:Endangered flora of Asia]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WolfmanSF", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dryobalanops_beccarii"}
